abstract: As the next debates loom, the progressive wing of the party wants sweeping change. Many others just want to jettison the president.
snippet: As the next debates loom, the progressive wing of the party wants sweeping change. Many others just want to jettison the president.
lead_paragraph: WAUKEE, Iowa — Bernie Sanders preaches “political revolution” to the crowds at his campaign rallies. Elizabeth Warren promises “big, systemic change” as she rolls out major policy proposals. And Pete Buttigieg warns his packed town hall audiences that the “riskiest thing we could do is try too hard to play it safe.”

headline_main: Why Democrats Are So Far From Consensus on 2020

byline_original: By Reid J. Epstein and Lisa Lerer

abstract: The Democratic candidate wants relevant policy, not “a beautiful sonnet.” Is that enough for voters?
snippet: The Democratic candidate wants relevant policy, not “a beautiful sonnet.” Is that enough for voters?
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — At her strongest, Senator Kamala Harris is forceful and pragmatic. She elates crowds in Iowa and South Carolina with her denunciations of President Trump, and spells out her policy agenda — on matters like restricting gun sales, reducing prescription drug prices and giving tax benefits to renters — in precise terms.

abstract: The 2020 Democrats reacted to the Mueller testimony, candidates tried out attacks before next week’s debates and Joe Biden received some good news.
snippet: The 2020 Democrats reacted to the Mueller testimony, candidates tried out attacks before next week’s debates and Joe Biden received some good news.
lead_paragraph: Every Saturday morning, we’re publishing “This Week in the 2020 Race”: a quick way to catch up on the presidential campaign and the field of 24 candidates for the Democratic nomination.

abstract: Ms. Warren is only the second Democratic candidate to cross the threshold this cycle, suggesting that relying on grass-roots fund-raising has paid off.
snippet: Ms. Warren is only the second Democratic candidate to cross the threshold this cycle, suggesting that relying on grass-roots fund-raising has paid off.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts has received one million donations to her campaign for president, her team said on Friday, making her the only Democratic candidate aside from Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont to announce reaching that threshold in the 2020 cycle.

abstract: The most direct confrontation of the campaign yet is unfolding as candidates battle for the support of black voters and the next debate rapidly approaches.
snippet: The most direct confrontation of the campaign yet is unfolding as candidates battle for the support of black voters and the next debate rapidly approaches.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr. entered the 2020 presidential campaign with wide support from black voters and a reservoir of good will stemming from his eight years as an unswervingly loyal vice president to Barack Obama — a huge head start in a primary where African-Americans will play a decisive role.

abstract: The federal government has not executed anyone since 2003, but the attorney general announced that five inmates will be put to death starting in December.
snippet: The federal government has not executed anyone since 2003, but the attorney general announced that five inmates will be put to death starting in December.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The federal government will resume executions of death row inmates after a nearly two-decade hiatus, Attorney General William P. Barr said Thursday, countering a broad national shift away from the death penalty as public support for capital punishment has dwindled.
